description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calling all experienced nurses and student nurses about to qualify! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are actively recruiting to the Medicine Division at UHNM into band 5 nursing roles to a variety of specialities. We are searching for people who are highly motivated to improving and achieving excellence in care delivery, diligence in patient safety, as well as care and compassion in abundance!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be about to qualify or already be a registered nurse who exemplifies the UHNM values of ‘Caring’, ‘Improving’, ‘Safe’ and ‘Together’. We particularly welcome applications from nurses who have been out of the Acute Trust for a while and are seeking to return, bringing with them all the expertise they have learned along the way!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would very much like you to join us and help us reach our goals on our journey to excellence. We have a variety of opportunities in the following departments across both Royal Stoke and County sites:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Emergency Department&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acute Medicine (including AMU, AEC, Short stay)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Specialised medicine (including renal, gastroenterology, respiratory)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Elderly care and general medicine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a comprehensive induction package and the opportunity to excel and exceed in your chosen field with a proactive PDR and development plan. Why not come and see what we have to offer?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rotational posts and self-rostering are available in many areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What next?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would welcome you for an informal chat at prior to the closing of this advert. Due to social distancing measures we can also offer this via Microsoft Teams if you would prefer. We can arrange virtual or telephone meetings with staff from your chosen medicine speciality, if you have particular passion for Acute, Emergency, General or Older Persons’ Medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carol Lloyd-Bennet - DACN&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;carola.lloyd-bennett@uhnm.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01782 674594&lt;/p&gt;
